prompt: Explain the significance of the moon landing.
answer:
Explain the significance of the moon landing.

On Friday, July 12, 1961, the Apollo 11 vehicle that broke ground on the moon crashed into the Pacific Ocean, killing all crew members aboard the spacecraft.

The first person to die during the mission before the landing was the Apollo 11 crewmate, Lt. Mitchell Mitchell, who passed away on July 24, 1961.

All of the other crew members, including Mitchell's commanding officer, Richard T. Davis Jr., will not be named, but will be remembered as "the people's hero."

This honor, while not formally mentioned in the memorial, was given by Armstrong during the Apollo 11 mission.

"When you are at Apollo 11, you get ready to be honored. You know you are going to be honored for four years, four years," he said.

Armstrong was so proud of his crew that he sent a memo about the day's events to the nation's chief astronauts to express his wish to "get back on the moon and continue doing this mission to the moon."
